All the pet changes are great, but remember one thing, they helped all pet classes. These were not magician specific changes, they were pet changes.<br>
<br>
Necro and magician pets both hit harder now.<br>
<br>
All pets in game are non aggro.<br>
<br>
All pets can now hear commands zone wide.<br>
<br>
All pet classes (except BL) summon a pet at the highest level each time.<br>
<br>
No pet takes experience if the caster does 1 point of damage.<br>
<br>
These changes are as I said great. Magician's relie upon their pets more than the other classes, but necros can and do relie upon pets when fear kitting etc.. and will now readily use a pet where they may not have in the past as it no longer sucks up even 1% of the experience.<br>
<br>
Once the pet haste cap is removed, all pets will benifit from the change, not just magician's except in the instance when frenzied burnout is cast.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, as I sdaid I applaud the changes, but our spells need to be looked at and re-evaluated. <br>
<br>
