<br>
But I think it might be, that most of us as our mages grew up in the pre-50 game, found our leveling abilities to be adequate... if not superior than most of our compatriots in other classes.<br>
<br>
Sure, I was 50 shortly after Kunark was launched, and there wasn't the variety of droppable/tradable weapons or armor that there is now, but even now, versus warriors, rangers or even monks, our soloability is fantatstic and our damage output via pets in groups is awesome pre-50 (especially 39 - 49).<br>
<br>
All of these were acceptable even before the recent changes (no exp penalty, max pet level summoning, etc.). Those changes would certainly keep us current mostly with the increases other classes have gotten via gear in recent expansions.<br>
<br>
For this reason, I think that the complaints from our younger mages are discounted. They have had it easier than we ever did... and we didn't have it that bad then.<br>
<br>
I think that's where some of the credibility issues come in. Either that, or I'm an old fart complaining about these young &quot;whippersnappers&quot; and how easy they have it today. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table width=100%><tr><td width=33%><font color=blue><i><b>Master Svenuce Summonstuff</b></i></font><br>
